<br>
What are the pros and cons of playing on a PvE server vs. a PvP server?  Add your own.<br>
<br>
PvE Pros:<br>
<br>
1)  You don't care about that damned crossteaming thing.<br>
2)  You get to level anywhere you want.<br>
3)  You get better gear.<br>
4)  You don't have to worry about getting killed by other players as much.<br>
<br>
PvE Cons:<br>
<br>
1)  You can't kill other players except by training them or /dueling them, or maybe fooling them into coming into an arena.<br>
2)  Leveling has always been pretty boring.<br>
3)  The challenge of achieving truly uber status on a PvE server is not nearly as hard.<br>
<br>
PvP Pros:<br>
<br>
1)  You can kill other players who aren't on your team.<br>
2)  Any accomplishments you make are great, because everything's more difficult.<br>
<br>
PvP Cons:<br>
<br>
1)  The teams are messed up.<br>
2)  The classes aren't balanced.<br>
3)  If you get enough loot whores together, and if they don't give a damn about the PnP, they will be the undisputed masters of the server.<br>
4)  Elves.<br>
5)  Shorts.<br>
6)  There are certain zones that are practically impossible to explore if you are a certain race.<br>
7)  You have to deal with level 60 players with bought accounts crowing on and on about how much they 0wn3d j0o after killing your sorry level 52 self.<br>
